\p \k Salak:\k*
\li2 1 Ti 2:5
\p \k Samaritan:\k*
\li2 Palestine prae thungah kaom Samaria prae thung ih kami. Samaritannawk loe Judahnawk mah hnukma o; tipongah tih nahaeloe nihcae loe Judah kami ai ah minawk kalah to zu ah lak o. Samaria kaminawk loe Judahnawk mah Sithaw bokhaih hoi kanghmong ah sithaw to bok o ai. Toe Jesu mah loe Samaritan kaminawk khaeah Sithaw prae kawng to patuk pae (Lk 10:25-37; 17:11-19; Jn 4:1-42)
\p \k Sang:\k*
\li2 Lk 24:49; Fi 3:14
\p \k Sanghaih:\k*
\li2 Ro 8:39; Ef 3:18
\p \k Sang kue:\k*
\li2 Lk 2:14; He 7:26
\p \k Sangqum boih:\k*
\li2 Mt 9:21; Mk 5:5:34; Tk 9:34
\p \k Saning (saningnawk): \k*
\li2 Lk 4:19; 2 Pi 3:8; Lp 20:2
\p \k Saoek padaphaih:\k*
\li2 Ef 6:14; 1 Th 5:8
\p \k Saphaw (pakoeh): \k*
\li2 Jn 12:43; Ef 1:6; He 13:15
\p \k Saphawhaih (pakoehhaih): \k*
\li2 Lk 2:13; 1 Pi 2:9
\p \k Saphaw (pakoeh): \k*
\li2 Mt 5:16; Jn 7:39; 12:28; 17:1; Tk 3:13; Ro 1:21; 1 Kr 6:20; 1 Pi 2:12
\p \k Sava:\k*
\li2 Mk 10:12; 1 Kr 7:14; 2 Kr 11:2; Ef 5:23; 5:25; Kol 3:19; 1 Pi 3:1
\p \k Savuet:\k*
\li2 Mt 7:26
\p \k Setan:\k*
\li2 Misa, tiah thuih koehhaih ih ni. Aling kami, tiah doeh thui thaih. Setan loe Sithaw ih misa ah oh. Sithaw mah sak ih hmuennawk boih phraek han koeh. Anih to taqawksae, tiah doeh kawk (Ja 4:7), kasae maeto (1Jn 5:18-19), hae long angraeng (Jn 14:30), vaihi dung ih sithaw (2Kr 4:4). Setan loe hae long nuiah sethaih sinkung ah oh. Anih loe lok amlai kami ah oh moe, Sithaw ih kaminawk parokung ah oh (Jn 8:42-47; 2 Kr 11:13-15; Lp 12). Setan mah paro tangcae sak pakhrai han ih ni Jesu loe hae long nuiah angzoh. Setan mah Jesu to pakaa han amsak. Toe Jesu loe Sithaw Capa ah oh pongah, Setan pong thacak kue (Mt 4:1-11; Mk 3:20-30; Tk 26:15-18; 1 Jn 3:7-8). Jesu hnukbangnawk loe Angraeng ih thacakhaih hnikhaih rang hoiah Setan to pakaa thaih (Ef 6:10-18; 1 Pi 5:8-11). Hnukkhuem niah loe Sithaw mah Setan to pazawk tih (Lp 20:1-10)
\p \k Setan:\k*
\li2 Mt 4:10; 16:23; Lk 22:3; Tk 26:18; Ro 16:20; 2 Kr 12:7
\p \k Sethaih (kasae):\k*
\li2 Mt 5:11; 6:34; 7:11; Jn 3:19; Ro 7:19; 12:21; 1 Kr 13:5; Ef 5:16; 1 Th 5:15; 1 Ti 6:10; 3 Jn 1:11
\p \k Setsakhaih (sethaih):\k*
\li2 Kol 3:8; 1 Pi 2:1
\p \k Siangpahrang:\k*
\li2 Lk 23:2; 1 Ti 6:15; Lp 19:16
\p \k Siangpahrangnawk:\k*
\li2 Lk 22:25; Lp 1:6
\p \k Sineko:\k*
\li2 Grik lok hoi “nawnto amkhueng” tih haih ih ni. Judahnawk loe bokhaih im ah Sithaw bok han hoi kaciim cabu lok amtuk hanah amkhueng o. Nawktanawk thuitaek moe, patuk hanah Sineko to patoh o. Jesu doeh Sithaw bok moe, kaminawk patuk hanah Sineko ah caeh toeng (Mk 1:21-28; Lk 4:14-30; Jn 12:37-43; 18:19-21). Pawl loe Judahnawk khaeah tamthanglok hoih taphong hanah Sineko to patoh (Tk 17:1-4, 10-12; 18:1-11)
\p \k Sinh:\k*
\li2 Mt 3:10; Lk 6:43; Mt 1:21; Lk 2:10; Jn 12:24; 1 Pi 3:18
\p \k Situi:\k*
\li2 Mt 25:8; He 1:9
\p \k Sithaw:\k*
\li2 Mt 6:24; 19:17; Jn 1:1; 17:3; Ro 8:31; 15:13; 1 Kr 15:28; 2 Kr 1:3; 1 Pi 5:10; 1 Jn 4:12
