\iot Z
\p \k Zae (zaehaih): \k*
\li2 Sithaw ih lok aek, Sithaw ih kaalok phraek. Zae tiah thuih ih lok loe Sithaw hoi angkomhaih amro pacoengah kaom lok ni. Zae loe kami sak tangsuek na hoiah om ai. Sak hmaloe ih kami khaeah Sithaw lok tahngaih han koeh maw, koeh ai, tiah qoih thaihaih to paek. Vaihi aicae loe zaehaih thungah tapen o moe, zaehaih misong ah a oh o boih (Mk 7:20-23; Ro 1:18-32; 3:9-20, 23; Ef 2:1-3). Zae thacakhaih to pazawk moe, zae pongah danpaekhaih takhoe ving hanah Jesu to patoeh (Ro 5-6; 2 Kr 5:21; Kol 2:13-15; 1 Ti 1:15-16; He 9:11; 10:18; 1 Jn 1:5; 2:2; 3:1-10). Sithaw kaminawk zaehaih taphong o naah nihcae to Sithaw mah tahmen tih (Lk 18:9-14; 1 Jn 1:9). Hnukkhuem niah loe Sithaw mah zaehaih pongah kaom hmuennawk boih to la ving tih (2Pi 3:10-13; Lp 21:1-5)
\p \k Zaehaih:\k*
\li2 Ro 3:19; 5:12; 6:14; 4:15; 1 Kr 11:27; Jn 1:47; 1:29; 1 Th 2:3; 2 Kr 5:21; Ef 4:26; 1 Jn 1:8; 3:9
